		<td><b>Twin Dragons Kickstarter !</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi everyone !<br /><br />I'm so happy to announce the launch of the Twin Dragons Kickstarter campaign !<br /><br />You can now support the project and help us release another homebrew for the NES.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1454702417/twin-dragons-a-brand-new-game-for-the-nes" class="postlink">https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1454702417/twin-dragons-a-brand-new-game-for-the-nes</a><br />(English subtitles available for the presentation video)<br /><br /><img src="https://ksr-ugc.imgix.net/assets/016/427/243/4919caeeba08ded348a536df7d05072b_original.jpg?w=680&amp;fit=max&amp;v=1493305381&amp;auto=format&amp;q=92&amp;s=de2469463ca96341e9360351d8bebd4d" alt="Image" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Erockbrox</b> [ Tue May 02, 2017 7:22 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Twin Dragons Kickstarter !</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The game looks outstanding and you are an amazing programmer!<br /><br />[edit]<br /><br />Okay I finally got a change to play the demo. Here are my notes and thoughts. <br /><br />- On the title screen only the select button can scroll down the menu options and the buttons B and A do not function. This should most likely be changed. The                                                                             up and down arrows should also scroll through the menu options and the B and A buttons should work the same as the start button for confirming things. <br /><br />- Why not add a charge shot fireball as an additional weapon? A fireball that when charged (B button held down) for a few seconds that is more powerful and can go through several enemies before dissipating.<br /><br />- When you die you go to a continue screen.  Yes, is on the left and No is one the right, however if you press left or right on the D-pad it does nothing. So the left and right buttons probably should be implemented here instead of just using select to choose your option. Also B and A do not confirm your option, this should probably be implemented too. <br /><br />- The first boss that you fight that looks like a stacked green ball cactus. If you beat the boss, but then get killed by the falling into the water the game freezes with a black screen. <br /><br />- I love the intro level screens. Reminds me of the Sonic 1,2 games. <br /><br />- Had no idea that pressing UP + B shoots the special item fireball. Maybe state this somewhere so players know. <br /><br />- Music and graphics are outstanding.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


